post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When weed was legalized in Colorado for recreational use, the [usage rate](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colorado-marijuana-idUSKCN0Z702N) among teens and children stayed the same. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalised, all the ways it could harm other people could be criminalised, such as taking them before controlling dangerous machinery or smoking in public. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In a free society, drug users must be free to share their perspective with others, and other people must be free to decide for themselves how they want to act.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't necessarily mean drugs should be legalized. Alternatively, we could make alcohol, cigarettes and fast food illegal. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If psychoactive medicine were properly administered and regulated, it could function in this religious/transcendental function, without causing personal and societal dysfunction. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Drug trafficking](https://www.cnbc.com/2013/08/09/Organized-crime:-Worlds-most-lucrative-criminal-activities.html?slide=1) is the most lucrative form of illicit business, worth about $2.1 trillion per year.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates with criminality, thievery, and risky sexual behavior. Responsibility is a state that is easily bypassed when you enter the flow of the drug world.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'They would have died on those drugs whether or not they were legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates with criminality, thievery, and risky sexual behavior. Responsibility is a state that is easily bypassed when you enter the flow of the drug world.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many currently illegal drugs make substantial positive contributions to human culture. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Those with unstable backgrounds are more likely to use drugs which are associated with withdrawal from society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[In German law](http://www.emcdda.europa.eu/countries/drug-reports/2018/germany/drug-laws-and-drug-law-offences_en), the use of drugs is not mentioned as a legal offense.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A higher number of drugs users will create more work for the accident and emergency paramedic services that have to deal with people who have overdosed due to improper usage.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The highest tax estimates of marijuana legalisation reach[$28 billion](https://taxfoundation.org/marijuana-tax-legalization-federal-revenue/) from federal revenues, business taxes and income taxes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Tobacco companies are investing in and moving to different technologies \\(vaping\\) as the population becomes more aware of the harms and less prone to tobacco smoking. They can tell tobacco smoking is ultimately a ‘sinking ship' for their profits."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police — this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Heroin users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/what-are-medical-complications-chronic-heroin-use) experience mental disorders, such as depression, insomnia and antisocial personality disorder.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising strong opioids such as heroin would only exacerbate the opioid crisis.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The additional tax revenue from drug commerce can be used to fund therapies and treatments. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of the appeal to rebellious teens is the fact that drug use is illegal. Treating moderated drug use as a normalized behavior and treating addiction/binge use as disease takes much of the "cool" factor away. That\'s why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The argument that illicit drugs can lead to addiction and should therefore be banned is a double standard, as various legal activities and substances are equally or even more addictive. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking the stigma and secrecy away from drug taking would mean family and friends would notice drug abuse earlier and be able to intervene.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Such stress might be irrational, especially when it's related to unproblematic drug use. In that case, the psychological stress is the fault of the persons irrational beliefs."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When people overdose on illegal drugs medical staff may have a problem knowing what's in the drugs that were ingested. If drugs were legal and regulated, they could save more lives."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's easier to regulate established companies in a legal market than it is in the black market. Any issue would be with bad regulations, not legalization. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
